<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n08177a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n08" href="#n08177a">N08 (VI.B.6)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n08all.htm#n08177a"> 177(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> young John lord / Rehoboam</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">As early as 1177 he appointed his youngest son John king of Ireland, and seems to have fully formed the intention of sending him over as a permanent governor or viceroy, a purpose which the misconduct of that youthful Rehoboam, as Giraldus calls him, was chiefly instrumental in foiling. <small> Emily Lawless, <a name="ELIS" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#ELIS"><cite title="source">Ireland (Story of Nations series</cite></a> (192?) 94</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
